- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0008-76362954
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0008
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    - business associate
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized sale of protected health information
  conditions:
  - pursuant to and in compliance with § 164.508(a)(4)
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The provider and business associate must not sell protected health information.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Clear prohibition but proving a ‘sale’ requires business-transaction artifacts
      (logs/configs); no observable oracle is specified to verify absence of sales.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0010-f798bb5b
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0010
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    - business associate
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI use or disclosure
  conditions:
  - for conducting a criminal, civil, or administrative investigation into any person
    for the mere act of seeking, obtaining, providing, or facilitating reproductive
    health care
  exceptions:
  - Subject to paragraphs (a)(5)(iii)(B) and (C) of this section
  requirements:
  - Entity and business associate must not use or disclose protected health information
    to conduct a criminal, civil, or administrative investigation into any person
    for the mere act of seeking, obtaining, providing, or facilitating reproductive
    health care.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Requires proving recipient investigative intent and ‘‘mere act’’ linkage,
      not objectively verifiable from standard logs or I/O.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
