- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0011-568c5985
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0011
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - activity is in connection with any person seeking, obtaining, providing, or facilitating
    reproductive health care
  - 'entity has reasonably determined that one or more of the following exists: (1)
    the reproductive health care is lawful under the law of the state in which such
    health care is provided under the circumstances in which it is provided; (2) the
    reproductive health care is protected, required, or authorized by Federal law
    under the circumstances in which such health care is provided; (3) the presumption
    at paragraph (a)(5)(iii)(C) of this section applies'
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - entity must apply the prohibition at paragraph (a)(5)(iii)(A) only when the activity
    is in connection with any person seeking, obtaining, providing, or facilitating
    reproductive health care and the entity reasonably determines that one or more
    of the listed conditions exists.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Requires a subjective 'reasonable determination' and references external
      'listed conditions'; no objective artifact or threshold to verify compliance.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
    - log_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0011-80e5fd5f
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0011
  scope:
    actor:
    - business associate
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - activity is in connection with any person seeking, obtaining, providing, or facilitating
    reproductive health care
  - 'business associate has reasonably determined that one or more of the following
    exists: (1) the reproductive health care is lawful under the law of the state
    in which such health care is provided under the circumstances in which it is provided;
    (2) the reproductive health care is protected, required, or authorized by Federal
    law under the circumstances in which such health care is provided; (3) the presumption
    at paragraph (a)(5)(iii)(C) of this section applies'
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - business associate must apply the prohibition at paragraph (a)(5)(iii)(A) only
    when the activity is in connection with any person seeking, obtaining, providing,
    or facilitating reproductive health care and the business associate reasonably
    determines that one or more of the listed conditions exists.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
