- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0018-61902715
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0018
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized disclosure of deceased individual's PHI
  conditions:
  - for a period of 50 years following the death of the individual
  - with respect to the protected health information of a deceased individual
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Entity must comply with the requirements of this subpart with respect to the protected
    health information of a deceased individual for a period of 50 years following
    the death of the individual.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Specifies actor, target data, and 50-year retention — verifiable via retention/config,
      dataset metadata, and access logs.
    evidence_signals:
    - config_check
    - data_check
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0018-ddf8d4f1
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0018
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: improper denial of access to PHI
  conditions:
  - as specified in this paragraph
  exceptions:
  - except as provided in paragraphs (g)(3) and (g)(5) of this section
  requirements:
  - Entity must treat a personal representative as the individual for purposes of
    this subchapter.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Entity's obligation is verifiable via policy/config, access logs, or I/O
      showing personal representative granted individual's PHI rights.
