- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0008-56c70832
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r/sent_0008
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - submitted document has any of the 45 CFR Part 164 Subpart E (up to date as of
    9/29/2025) Privacy of Individually Identifiable Health Information 45 CFR 164.508(a)(2)
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - org must not accept or rely on an authorization as valid if the submitted document
    has any of the 45 CFR Part 164 Subpart E (up to date as of 9/29/2025) Privacy
    of Individually Identifiable Health Information 45 CFR 164.508(a)(2).
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Verify by inspecting submitted document for 45 CFR 164.508(a)(2) text
      and observing org's accept/reject decision in I/O.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0009-bfe96ba8
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r/sent_0009
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: creation of compound authorization
  conditions:
  - authorization for the use or disclosure of protected health information
  exceptions:
  - authorization for the use or disclosure of protected health information for a
    research study may be combined with any other type of written permission for the
    same or another research study
  requirements:
  - The entity shall not combine an authorization for the use or disclosure of protected
    health information with any other document to create a compound authorization.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: No specified artifact/metadata or objective check to detect whether authorization
      documents were combined (no concrete oracle defined).
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0010-d7b0c9cc
  source:
