- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-fcbcdfd7
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-509-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-attestation-is-req
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-509-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-attestation-is-req/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: individuals uninformed of consequences of refusing authorization
  conditions:
  - when, in accordance with paragraph (b)(4) of this section, the covered entity
    can condition treatment, enrollment in the health plan, or eligibility for benefits
    on failure to obtain such authorization
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The provider shall state the consequences to the individual of a refusal to sign
    the authorization when, in accordance with paragraph (b)(4) of this section, the
    provider can condition treatment, enrollment in the health plan, or eligibility
    for benefits on failure to obtain such authorization.
  evidence:
  - authorization
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Obligation requires providers to state consequences; presence of such
      statement can be verified by inspecting authorization forms/communications.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
