  hazard: missing reference to covered entity notice
  conditions:
  - to the extent that the information in paragraph (c)(2)(i)(A) of this section is
    included in the notice required by § 164.520
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The provider shall include a reference to the covered entity's notice when the
    information in paragraph (c)(2)(i)(A) of this section is included in the notice
    required by § 164.520.
  evidence:
  - notice
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Can inspect notices to verify when specified info appears the provider
      included the covered entity's notice reference.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-4d7bff1b
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-509-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-attestation-is-req
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-509-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-attestation-is-req/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: uninformed authorization
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - entity must ensure that the authorization is written in plain language.
  evidence:
  - authorization (plain language)
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: ‘Plain language’ is subjective and lacks an objective metric/threshold,
      so pass/fail cannot be determined.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-fa1abc82
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-509-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-attestation-is-req
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-509-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-attestation-is-req/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - when the entity seeks an authorization from an individual for a use or disclosure
    of protected health information
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - entity must provide the individual with a copy of the signed authorization when
    it seeks an authorization for a use or disclosure of protected health information.
  evidence:
  - signed authorization (copy provided)
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Verify by checking logs or records proving a signed authorization copy
      was delivered to the individual.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0003-7a049993
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-509-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-attestation-is-req
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-509-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-attestation-is-req/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    - business associate
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - for purposes specified in § 164.512(d), (e), (f), or (g)(1)
  - without obtaining an attestation valid under paragraph (b)(1)
  - without complying with all applicable conditions of this part
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Entity and business associate shall not use or disclose protected health information
    potentially related to reproductive health care for the purposes specified in
    § 164.512(d), (e), (f), or (g)(1) unless they obtain an attestation valid under
    paragraph (b)(1) and comply with all applicable conditions of this part.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Disclosures can be detected in logs/outputs and attestation presence/validity
      can be checked in records/config.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - config_check
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0004-3106674b
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-509-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-attestation-is-req
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-509-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-attestation-is-req/sent_0004
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - org must ensure that a valid attestation is a document that meets the requirements
    of paragraph (c)(1) of this section.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Can inspect attestation documents and verify they meet the explicit paragraph
      (c)(1) requirements.
    evidence_signals:
    - data_check
